Text.Value: What does she want with you?
Karlach, who's Flo?
'Fraid they're all gone. Should've come around sooner.
Enough - I want to trade, not chat.
Cambion. But you're right. Then again... they could really come in handy.
Didn't need to. Your Flo did some devil woo-woo and stuck 'em in my head. Couldn't forget now if I wanted to.
D'you want the coins or not?
A shit-eating grin. Oh, and uh. This. That's it.
Let me see your wares.
That's all.
That's all?

EditorData.NodeContext: A little sadly while maintaining her tough exterior

Text.Value: For every coin you take, you've got to hear the story of the soul trapped inside.
She got what she asked for. A fellow named Clint, destined to be her soul mate. Struck by a cart and died a few moments after clapping eyes on our Mavery. Poor guy.
Well. Flo didn't tell a lie. She said you'd find me, and here you are. Karlach, isn't it?
Florenta the Garrotter. A cambion I knew back in Avernus.
Sure you will.
She came dressed as a novice. Gave me three soul coins. Said I could sell 'em if I wanted, but if I kept 'em for you, she'd consider it a favour owed.
We'll put that coin to better use than Tiamat would've.
Frakes called out for help - prayed for his children to have meat to eat.
Next coin, please.
I'll explain later - away from prying ears. But trust me - you'll be into it.

EditorData.NodeContext: Referring to why she wants to collect soul coins

Text.Value: Let's hope it doesn't come to that. What did she want, anyway?

EditorData.NodeContext: 'What did she want anyway' is directed to the NPC

Text.Value: You can take a look at my other wares, if you like. Won't entice Flo into my debt, but I'm always looking for wielders worthy of my stock.
No - that's final.
What's a soul coin?
Let me see your wares.
Well thanks, Flo. Hearing a bunch of desperate horror has ruined my day, which I suppose was the point.
Next coin, please.
Now there's a name I'd hoped never to hear again. What was Flo doing here?
He should've known. Better to die a thousand deaths than let Zariel into your life.
Better hope you can handle what I've got.
Infernal currency - each one is inscribed with a soul. Usually an evil soul, but... not always.

EditorData.NodeContext: A little sheepish on the 'not always' since Karlach consumes soul coins

Text.Value: You got three soul coins out of the bargain, didn't you? I'd quit whinging if I were you.
You can take a look at the rest of my lot, if you like. Got good weapons in search of a worthy wielder.
Didn't think to quiz her about her business.
Whatever you need to tell yourself.
I did my part. That means our business is done, unless you've got actual gold to hand.
Leave.
Let's have the soul coins, then.
The scud of her soul is yours, now.
That's absolutely vile. Unsurprising of Zariel, but vile all the same.
I'd tell you another, but I'm afraid that's the only coin I've got for you. You should've come around sooner while I still had all three.
Fine. Get on with it, then.
That fact that she knows where I am - where I might be going - doesn't exactly delight me.
We shouldn't take anything offered by a devil. Too risky.
Pfft. All right. Suit yourself. Have a trade or whatever. Then let's get out of here.

EditorData.NodeContext: Player is being dismissive of her.

Text.Value: Memorised a bunch of sad stories on her behalf, did you?
Last one's got the soul of a little boy named Ongir. Eight years old. He liked playing in the sun with his friends. That's all I know.

EditorData.NodeContext: ON-geer but it's a one-off so do it your way

Text.Value: Soul coins, huh? Those could come in handy.

EditorData.logicalname: Knows about Karlach's use for soul coins.

Text.Value: Enough chatter. Your friend gave me three soul coins. Said I could sell 'em if I wanted, but if I kept 'em for you, she'd consider it a favour owed.
What did this person want with Karlach?
She was born to a cruel mother and a violent father and three evil brothers, all named Baldur.
Soul coins, huh? I know this is odd, but I could make good use of those. Might as well take 'em, while they're on offer.

EditorData.logicalname: Doesn't know about Karlach's use for soul coins

Text.Value: She came dressed as a novice. Gave me three soul coins. Said I could sell 'em if I wanted, but if I kept 'em for your friend, she'd consider it a favour owed.
I'd tell you another, but I'm afraid those are the only coins I've got for you. You should've come around sooner while I still had all three.
We're just getting started.
This'n has got the soul of a man named Frakes. Lived in a village near Neverwinter, hit hard by the worst hunger in a thousand years.
She was the closest thing I had to a friend. That said, she would've choked the life out of me if I ever turned my back on her.
I've got all sorts on offer, if you're worthy of 'em.
If she rears her head, we'll handle her.
Sure. But she did have a condition.

EditorData.NodeContext: A condition before Karlach can have the soul coins

Text.Value: What do you want soul coins for?
I wouldn't have given her the time of day, but even I needed a laugh once in a while. And what can I say, the bitch had good jokes.
Nothing would surprise me. Maybe she wants to live up to her name and wrap a cord around my neck. Or maybe she just wants to say hello.
No - we're not playing her little game.
Zariel answered. Made old Frakes grow flesh upon flesh after flesh. His wee ones had all the meat they could stomach.
Leave.
Karlach's the one set to consume his soul, I hear.
Leave.
That's all. Oh. And this slip of scratch.
Maybe. Probably. I don't know. She's a half-devil. Impossible to read.
There you have it. Flo came all this way just to try to make me feel like shit. Clever use of her time.
Is she a threat?
Suit yourself.

EditorData.NodeContext: A bit put out cause the player is short-cutting an origin moment.

Text.Value: She never knew a day of love in all her life. When she was a girl of fifteen, she sold her soul to Tiamat in exchange for someone who would love her unconditionally.
She said Karlach might say that. And she said to let her have it her own way.
First coin's got the soul of a woman named Mavery.

EditorData.NodeContext: MAH- vur-ee. Only here so pronounce it however you want.

Text.Value: That's a sad story indeed.
Thanks, I guess.

EditorData.NodeContext: A bit chastened but still with a hard edge.

Text.Value: We'll put his coin to good use. He'll help us rid the Realms of people like Zariel.
Did Flo have anything else for us?
Oh, gods damn it!

Synopsis: Karlach meets Lann at MOO and he offers her three soul coins as long as she hears the stories of their souls.
